  "prompt": "How can I recover deleted photos from app lock new version?",
  "response": "Recovering deleted photos from an app like \"App Lock\" (which is typically used to secure other apps and their contents) can be challenging, but there are several methods you can try to retrieve your lost images. Here's a comprehensive guide to help you through the process:\n\n### **1. Check Within the App Itself**\n\n**a. In-App Recycle Bin or Trash:**\nSome app lockers have a built-in feature to temporarily store deleted files before permanent removal. Open the App Lock app and look for sections named \"Trash,\" \"Recycle Bin,\" or \"Deleted Files.\"\n\n**b. Backup Features:**\nCheck if the App Lock app has a backup feature. If you had previously enabled backups (either on the cloud or locally), you might be able to restore your photos from there.\n\n### **2. Explore Device Storage**\n\n**a. Hidden Folders:**\nApp lockers often store protected files in hidden directories. Use a file manager (like **Files by Google** for Android or **File Manager** on iOS) to navigate to the app\u2019s storage directory.\n\n- **For Android:**\n  - Connect your device to a computer via USB.\n  - Enable \"Show hidden files\" in your file manager settings.\n  - Navigate to **Internal Storage > Android > data > [App_Lock_Package_Name] > files** or a similar path.\n  \n- **For iOS:**\n  - iOS restricts direct file system access, but you can explore app data via iTunes or Finder backups on your computer.\n\n**b. Default Photo Folders:**\nSometimes, photos might still reside in the standard photo directories like **DCIM** or **Pictures**. Use your gallery app to check all albums, including any hidden ones.\n\n### **3. Use Data Recovery Software**\n\nIf the above methods don\u2019t work, data recovery tools can help retrieve deleted photos. Note that the success rate varies based on whether new data has overwritten the deleted files.\n\n**a. For Android Devices:**\n\n- **Dr.Fone - Data Recovery (Android):** [Link](https://drfone.wondershare.com/android-data-recovery.html)\n- **EaseUS MobiSaver for Android:** [Link](https://www.easeus.com/android-data-recovery-software/)\n\n**Steps:**\n1. Download and install the chosen software on your computer.\n2. Connect your Android device via USB and enable **USB Debugging** in Developer Options.\n3. Follow the on-screen instructions to scan your device for deleted photos.\n4. Preview and recover the desired images.\n\n**b. For iOS Devices:**\n\n- **Dr.Fone - Data Recovery (iOS):** [Link](https://drfone.wondershare.com/ios-data-recovery.html)\n- **iMobie PhoneRescue:** [Link](https://www.phonerescue.com/)\n\n**Steps:**\n1. Download and install the software on your computer.\n2. Connect your iPhone/iPad and choose the recovery mode.\n3. Scan your device or backups for deleted photos.\n4. Select and recover the needed images.\n\n### **4. Restore from Cloud Backups**\n\nIf you regularly back up your device or photos to cloud services, you might be able to recover deleted images from there.\n\n**a. Google Photos (Android):**\n- Open Google Photos app.\n- Go to **Library > Trash**.\n- Restore photos within 60 days of deletion.\n\n**b. iCloud (iOS):**\n- Visit [iCloud.com](https://www.icloud.com/) and sign in.\n- Go to **Photos > Recently Deleted**.\n- Recover photos within 30 days.\n\n**c. Other Cloud Services:**\nCheck services like Dropbox, OneDrive, or any other you might have used to back up photos.\n\n### **5. Contact App Support**\n\nIf the photos were exclusively managed by the App Lock app, reaching out to the app's customer support might provide specific solutions or insights into whether recovery is possible.\n\n### **6. Prevent Future Data Loss**\n\nOnce you've addressed the current issue, consider these steps to safeguard your photos moving forward:\n\n- **Regular Backups:** Use cloud services or local backups to ensure your photos are always saved elsewhere.\n- **Understand App Features:** Familiarize yourself with the app\u2019s functionalities to prevent accidental deletions.\n- **Use Reliable Apps:** Ensure you're using trusted app locker apps that offer robust backup and recovery features.\n\n### **Important Considerations**\n\n- **Act Quickly:** The sooner you attempt recovery after deletion, the higher the chances of success. Continued use of the device can overwrite the deleted data.\n- **Root or Jailbreak Risks:** Some recovery methods, especially on Android, might require rooting your device, which can void warranties and pose security risks. Proceed with caution.\n- **Data Privacy:** Ensure that any third-party software you use for recovery is reputable to protect your data privacy.\n\nBy following these steps, you increase your chances of successfully recovering deleted photos from the App Lock app. If you're unsure or uncomfortable performing any of these steps, consider seeking assistance from a professional data recovery service.",
